title: 5.7 quake shakes cordova, valdez
author: Ap
text: PALMER, Alaska - A 5.7-magnitude earthquake shook Prince William Sound last night.    The quake was felt in Cordova and Valdez, but there were no reports of damage or injuries, according to Wayne Jorgensen of the Tsunami Warning Center.     The quake was centered about 40 miles southwest of Cordova
